Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
generate_fence(25.10)                                    generate_fence(25.10)

Name
       generate_fence -
        Automatically  draws  partition fences that enclose all their children
       FlexModel guides

Syntax
       generate_fence

       [-help]

       [-flow {2G}]

       [-for_partition]

       [-rectangle_shape]

       [-target_util <float>]

       [ [-hInst {<hInst(s)>}] | [-module {<module(s)>}] | [-inst_group  {<in-
       stGroup(s)>}] ]

        Automatically  draws  partition fences that enclose all their children
       FlexModel guides.  It helps to improve the usability of the prototyping
       flow. The recommended use model for automatically generating fences  is
       as follows:

              * Run proto_design to place FlexModel guides/fences.

              * Manually adjust/move FlexModels to shorten timing paths.

              * Run  the following commands to analyze the floorplan and check
                timing. Repeat step 2 and 3 if needed

                * place_opt_design

                * earlyGlobalRoute

                * timeDesign -proto

                * load_timing_debug_report -proto

              * Select FlexModels for partitions and define partitions.

              * Run generate_fence to create fences  that  enclose  all  their
                children FlexModel guides.

       Note:  If  no option is specified then the command draws fences for all
       existing defined partitions.

Parameters
       -flow {2G}
              Enables the Auto-Fence Generation 2G  flow  to  draw  the  fence
              shapes  automatically.  When  this  flow  is enabled, the mixed-
              placement capability is leveraged to give optimal module  place-
              ment  distribution.  A fence is generated for each target module
              after considering target utilization, boundary gaps and I/Os.

              The Auto-Fence Generation 2G flow  involves  the  following  key
              steps:

              * Running flat global mixed placement

              * Creating the fence based on the module cells placement distri-
                bution and control the utilization.

              * Polishing the fence so not to block any channel or I/O access

              Data_type: float, optional

       -for_partition
              When  specified, it enables the partition fence generation capa-
              bility. When this option is  not  specified,  the  power  domain
              fence generation capability is enabled by default.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each generate_fence parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man generate_fence

       -hInst {<hInst(s)>}
              Specifies the  list  of  hierarchical  instance  names  to  draw
              fences.  This  option  can  be used if you only want to create a
              fence for a specific master or clone. You can use wildcards.

              Note: It can not be used for both master and clones.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -inst_group {<instGroup(s)>}
              Specifies list of instance group names to draw fences.  You  can
              use wildcards.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -module {<module(s)>}
              Specifies  list of partition modules to draw fences. This option
              should be used for master/clone partitions.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -rectangle_shape
              When specified, only rectangle shaped fences are generated.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -target_util <string>
              Specifies the fence target utilization value.

              Default: Core Utilization

              Min: 1e-07

              Max: 1

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
              *

                The following command enables  the  auto-fence  generation  2G
                flow and creates fences for the $PowerDomainNameList group.

                generate_fence -flow 2G -inst_group $PowerDomainNameList

              *

                The  following  command  enables  the auto-fence generation 2G
                flow  and  creates  fences  for  specified  hierarchical   in-
                stance(s).

                generate_fence -flow 2G -hInst $hInstNameList -for_partition

